Defendant Sarah C Lartz in court with attorney Ronald James Sonderhouse.  David John Behm appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant pleads guilty to counts 8 and 9.  Court finds the defendant guilty of counts 8 and 9.  Count 7 is dismsised outright. State makes recommendations.  Attorney Sonderhouse makes statements.  Defendant makes statements.  

The Court Orders the Following:  Count 8   
Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:
15 Days Huber with STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS.  Concurrent. (Credit - 5 days).  
Term of Probation: 1 Year
Conditions of Probation:
Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
No contact with co-defendants.   
AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
No Use or Possession of illegal controlled substances or drug paraphernalia;
Inform agent of all prescriptions;
Disclose to any physician in writing your conditions of probation. 
Sign Medical Release for Agent;
Fill all prescriptions at the same pharacy and allow agent to monitor prescriptions
COSTS:  $243.00 to be paid as a condition of probation
DNA Surcharge: $200.00 to be paid as a condition of probation
DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 

